U.S. Agriculture UndersecretaryDaniel Amstutz said he was confident that a European Community,EC, proposal to tax vegetable and marine oils and fats wouldnot be approved by the Community.    Asked by Reuters if he was confident the plan eventuallywould be defeated, Amstutz said, "Yes, I am, but I also knowthat things like this take constant vigilance."    The USDA official said the EC Council of Ministers held anad hoc meeting yesterday.    Commenting on that meeting, he said, "So far, so good."    Yesterday British Farm Minister Michael Jopling said enoughEC states appeared to be opposed to the proposals by thecommission for a 330 European Currency Unit a tonne tax onvegetable oils, fats and marine oils for the moves to bedefeated. Reuter&#3;